How to install MySQL on server:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install mysql-server
sudo systemctl start mysql.service
sudo mysql
ALTER USER 'root'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED WITH mysql_native_password BY 'password'; (‘password’ should be replaced with the desired password)

Using MySql

mysql -u root -p 
It will ask for your password that you set (point 5)
Once in, you can run all the MySQL commands.
Show tables;
